text: Roxanne Trunnell (born April 26, 1985) is an American Paralympic equestrian. She won three medals at the 2020 Summer Paralympics. She also got a gold medal at 2020 Summer Paralympics. She got a bronze medal in the team open event. Trunnell has H1N1 virus.
